main event: A white light was observed moving from west to east over the Pacific Ocean.
interesting points: The observation took place on December 16, 1963, at 0535Z., The object had a brightness comparable to a 29 magnitude star., The sighting lasted for 1 minute., It is suggested that the object may have been a satellite or stars not yet visible., The report is part of the U.S. Air Force's Project Blue Book which investigated UFOs.
sighted object: a white light in the sky
